      <p>I discovered the love of cooking later in life due to having no children and a husband who loved to cook (but not necessarily soups). The Smothered Cabbage Soup was the first of your offering that ended up in my favorite recipe inventory and is definitely tagged as comfort food. It was the first time I had used/eaten a head of cabbage other than the smooth green heads that thrived in my father&#8217;s carefully tended garden. My folks would turn them into yummy vats of pungent sauerkraut. It also introduced me to Arborio. Growing up, rice was rice in our house. It was always served with milk, sugar and raisins. My simple cooking mother would be amazed that I now have four types in my larder and use  them in savory dishes. I enjoy your blog, thanks.</p>
    </div>

