      <a href="https://orangette.net/2016/01/9228/#comment-45527"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2016-02-03T20:44:43-05:00">Wednesday, February 3, 2016 at 8:44 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Molly, I made your recipe this week!  Because I teach at a community college, I didn&#8217;t have the big time block available.  So I split the work into two evenings.  I made the ham stock the first night, refrigerated it overnight; the added benefit was that the fat gelled overnight, so I could remove it from the stock the next morning.  The next evening I prepared the rest of the soup.  It is divine!  My husband Joe, who doesn&#8217;t care for split peas, ate two bowls.  Thank you for your wonderful blog.  I always feel that I have stopped by a friend&#8217;s kitchen to chat.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-45527' data-commentid="45527" data-postid="9228" data-belowelement="comment-45527" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Kathleen" aria-label='Reply to Kathleen'>Reply</a>    </div>
