      <a href="https://orangette.net/2016/01/9228/#comment-45572"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2016-02-04T13:06:02-05:00">Thursday, February 4, 2016 at 1:06 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>You have hit on my two biggest beefs with Cook&#8217;s Illustrated/America&#8217;s Test Kitchen: long process, dirty dishes. But I still trust them with my whole heart. I will definitely be making this. I wonder if you&#8217;ve tried Melissa Clark&#8217;s recipe for gingery split pea soup with coriander (found in Cook This Now). It&#8217;s a good solution for those times you don&#8217;t have a ham bone hanging around. I recommend it!</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-45572' data-commentid="45572" data-postid="9228" data-belowelement="comment-45572" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Elizabeth" aria-label='Reply to Elizabeth'>Reply</a>    </div>
